Same error occured with rel-1.7.0
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/61653207/117289247-f4cbe100-ae9e-11eb-8cf5-a21ae41cc99a.png)

we also have an option where you can try building onnxruntime and skip the tests.

Just an additional flag **--skip_tests**

You can give it a try. In case, you want to avoid running the tests.
.\build.bat --config Release --build_shared_lib --use_openmp --use_openvino CPU_FP32   --build_wheel --cmake_generator "Visual Studio 16 2019" -**-skip_tests**

Also you can use --parallel to speed up the build process. This flag when used, uses all the cpu cores while building making the overall build time process quick.

.\build.bat --config Release --build_shared_lib --use_openmp --use_openvino CPU_FP32   --build_wheel --cmake_generator "Visual Studio 16 2019" **--parallel --skip_tests**

Resolved offline. Issue was that .dlls weren't generated in onnxruntime\build\Windows\Release\Release\onnxruntime\capi. Copying over the required onnxruntime_providers_(shared/openvino) dlls from the *\Release\Release folder and rebuilding fixed the issue.

Thanks for all your help. The problem was resolved. It might be related with 
```
if (onnxruntime_USE_OPENVINO)
  if(NOT WIN32)
    add_custom_command(
      TARGET onnxruntime_pybind11_state POST_BUILD
      COMMAND ${CMAKE_COMMAND} -E copy
          ${OPENVINO_DLL_PATH} $<TARGET_FILE:onnxruntime_providers_openvino>
          $<TARGET_FILE:onnxruntime_providers_shared>
          $<TARGET_FILE_DIR:${build_output_target}>/onnxruntime/capi/
    )
  endif()
endif()
```
in onnxruntime_python.cmake for version early than 1.7.0. It has been changed into 
```
if (onnxruntime_USE_OPENVINO)
    add_custom_command(
      TARGET onnxruntime_pybind11_state POST_BUILD
      COMMAND ${CMAKE_COMMAND} -E copy
          $<TARGET_FILE:onnxruntime_providers_openvino>
          $<TARGET_FILE:onnxruntime_providers_shared>
          $<TARGET_FILE_DIR:${build_output_target}>/onnxruntime/capi/
    )
endif()
```
in master branch and it can work. 

Thanks again.

Glad to hear that. Looks like the fix didn't go into onnxruntime 1.7 release. This  fix will be officially available with the next onnxruntime 1.8 release which is gonna be out after a week or so. For now, you can work with master.

please close the ticket if you don't have any other issues. @leqiao-1
